rComments: Made a genuine effort but wasn't good at explaining concepts or relating them to problems that we would be tested on. I switched to a different lecture eventually.

A very boring prof. Extremely hard to follow through his lectures. By the end of the lecture you would then realize that he's only trying to conclude to one main point after all the unorganized explanations and confusion. He could take an hour in explaining a simple theorem while TAs only need 5 min to explain the exact same thing.
If I can give a 0 I would. This prof doesn't want you to even be happy, just wants you to be depressed.

So, so hard to focus. The entire class is talking and he doesn't seem to care at all. His way of explaining things is a little difficult to understand too; disorganized and sort of all over the place, very hard to follow. He's a good prof if you want to train yourself "tunnel attention", if you just want to learn take someone else.
